<major-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2009-08-26.1.mh" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-09/wa0826.htm">Scottish Executive</major-heading>

<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2009-08-26.S3W-26219.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-09/wa0826.htm#1">Alcohol</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2009-08-26.S3W-26219.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80280" speakername="Bill Aitken (Glasgow) (Con)" spid="S3W-26219" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-09/wa0826.htm#1">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive how many offences of selling alcohol to under-18s have been detected in the last six months, broken down by police force; how many have resulted in a (a) prosecution and (b) conviction of licensees operating (i) on-sales and (ii) off-sales premises, and how many prosecutions for these offences are still pending.</p>

</ques>


