  <p>Notes:</p>

  <p>1. Charges where &quot;no action&quot; or &quot;no further action&quot; have been marked includes those cases for which there was found to be insufficient evidence to proceed.</p>

  <p>2. These tables include offences reported against licensees, their employees and their agents.</p>

  <p>3. The information for this question has been extracted from the Crown Office and Procurator Fiscal Service&rsquo;s Case Management Database. The database is a live, operational database used to manage the processing of reports submitted to procurators fiscal by the police and other reporting agencies. If a procurator fiscal amends a charge submitted by a reporting agency the database will record details only of the amended charge.</p>

  <p>4. The database is charge-based. The figures quoted therefore relate to the number of charges rather than the number of individuals charged or the number of incidents that gave rise to such charges.</p>

  <p>5. The information in these tables is correct as at 11th August 2009.</p>

